{{Infobox United States District Court Case
| name         = McLean v. Arkansas
| court        = [[United States District Court for the Eastern District of Arkansas]]
| full name    = McLean v. Arkansas Board of Education
| date decided = January 5, 1982
| citations    = [[Case citation|529]] [[F. Supp.]] [https://law.justia.com/cases/federal/district-courts/FSupp/529/1255/2354824/ 1255]
| transcripts  = [http://www.talkorigins.org/faqs/mclean-v-arkansas.html McLean v. Ark]
| judge        = [[William Overton (judge)|William Overton]]
| holding      = The Arkansas ''Balanced Treatment Act'' of 1981 requiring schools balance the teaching of evolution with the teaching of creation science violated the [[Establishment Clause of the First Amendment|Establishment Clause]] of the [[First Amendment to the United States Constitution]]
