In [[parliamentary government|parliamentary]] systems of government with [[multicameral]] [[legislature]]s, the '''responsible house''' is the [[Chambers of parliament|legislative chamber]] to which the government of the day is accountable (or ''responsible'', the origin of the term). A government remains in power as long as it retains the [[confidence (politics)|confidence]] of the responsible house.

