{{hatnote|This article is about the American law professor and Dean. For other people, see [[Edward Sell (disambiguation)]].}} {{Infobox scientist |name =W. Edward Sell |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |residence = |citizenship = |nationality = |ethnicity = |field =[[Business law]] |work_institutions =[[University of Pittsburgh School of Law]] |alma_mater = |doctoral_advisor = |doctoral_students = |known_for = |influences = |influenced = |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = }} '''W. Edward Sell''' (1923 – August 15, 2004) was the [[Dean (education)|Dean]] of the [[University of Pittsburgh School of Law]] from 1966 through 1977.
==Education== He graduated from [[Washington & Jefferson College]] in 1945.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.washjeff.edu/uploadedFiles/External_Relations/For_the_Media/mag_w05_classnotes.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2008-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110519022417/http://www.washjeff.edu/uploadedFiles/External_Relations/For_the_Media/mag_w05_classnotes.pdf |archive-date=2011-05-19 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> He earned his J.D. from [[Yale Law School]] in 1947.<ref>[http://mac10.umc.pitt.edu/u/FMPro?-db=ustory&-lay=a&-format=d.html&storyid=2189&-Find University Times<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
==Tenure at University of Pittsburgh School of Law== He became a professor at [[University of Pittsburgh School of Law]] in 1947. As a professor, he received the "Excellence in Teaching Award" in 1986.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.law.pitt.edu/faculty/awards|title=Faculty Awards - PittLaw|website=www.law.pitt.edu}}</ref> He served as [[Chair]] of the Administrative Committee from 1965 through 1966.
==Honors== [[Image:EdwardSellMemorialBarcoLawLobby.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Bronze bust and plaque honoring Edward Sell's 50th year of teaching at Pitt.]] Professor Douglas M. Branson is the current W. Edward Sell Professor of Business Law at the [[University of Pittsburgh School of Law]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.law.pitt.edu/faculty/profiles/branson|title=Douglas M. Branson - University of Pittsburgh School of Law<!-- Bot generated title -->|publisher=}}</ref>
The [[University of Pittsburgh]] chapter of the [[American Inns of Court]] is named after Sell.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.innsofcourt.org/Content/InnContent.aspx?Id=425|title=The University of Pittsburgh-W. Edward Sell American Inn of Court|website=www.innsofcourt.org}}</ref> He also the namesake of the [[American Inns of Court|American Inns of Court's]] "W. Edward Sell Inn Honors Professionalism Award."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.innsofcourt.org/Content/Default.aspx?Id=1647|title=Error: The document you requested does not exist.|website=www.innsofcourt.org}}</ref>
[[Washington & Jefferson College]] awards the "W. Edward Sell Legal Achievement Award" annually at [[homecoming]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washjeff.edu/content.aspx?section=860&menu_id=222&crumb=221&id=7524|title=W&J: Homecoming 2006<!-- Bot generated title -->|publisher=}}</ref>
